column2: There are spreadsheets by station and quarter hour,
for Weekday, Saturday and Sunday, both for entries and exits.
There is also a separate spreadsheet for total annual usage.
Number of passengers passing gates or ticket barriers
going from the street to the platforms
Number of passengers … going from the platforms to the street.
Usually an LU passenger, but for most joint stations the
count will include flows between the street and NR services.
Date of count - see also Source below
T = Figures include all passengers on the W&C line (which is closed on Sundays)
B = Figures for Bank/Monument now exclude W&C line passengers interchanging with other lines
A = previous year's counts adjusted by average change between years by zone
Every quarter hour of the day has a column.
Total for the whole traffic day
Bank and Monument are treated as a single station
All numbers quoted are number of passengers for one typical day.
Up to 1997 inclusive all count data was obtained by
field workers watching and counting the flow on one day -
this is called a manual count.
Increasingly since 1998, count data has been obtained from the automatic
gates.  This is processed through our RELATE computer system and is
based on an average over five weeks.
Where the date of the count is a single day or a season eg Aut-11, Spr-11 this
implies that the data comes from a manual count.
Where the date is given as a month this implies that gate data has been used, eg:
Nov-11 the five weeks (starting 31/10/11 and ending 02/12/11) and the thirteen weeks (03/09/11 to 26/11/11)  for weekend.
